{
  "text": "Bax is a member of the Bcl-2 family of proteins and plays a key role in the induction of apoptosis. In response to apoptotic stimuli, Bax translocates from the cytosol to mitochondria and causes release of apoptogenic factors [CITATION_1] . Inhibition of Bax would be extremely useful in islet culture immediately after isolation procedure. Ku70 plays an important role in DNA double-strand break repair in the nucleus [CITATION_2] . Ku70 binds Bax in the cytosol and inhibits its translocation into mitochondria [CITATION_3] . The Bax-binding ",
